<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl text-gray-800">
  <header class="mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-6">
      The Professional Guide to Home Construction Estimates: Building a Scalable Bidding System
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
      A home construction estimate is more than a calculation; it is a business-critical system. For scaling builders, the transition from individual expertise to a repeatable, software-driven process is the difference between surviving and thriving in a volatile market.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none prose-headings:text-gray-900 prose-headings:font-bold">
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl mb-4">Why Your Spreadsheet is the Ceiling on Your Growth</h2>
      <p>
        Most residential construction firms begin with a <%= link_to "master spreadsheet", static_page_path(slug: "home-construction-estimator"), class: "link link-primary" %>. It works for the first five builds, but as the company scales to fifty, the cracks begin to show. This "spreadsheet ceiling" is caused by three primary failures in the manual estimating process.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
        <div class="card bg-base-200 p-6 text-gray-800">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">The Expert Bottleneck</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">When pricing depends on the founder's intuition, the company cannot bid faster than one person can think.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card bg-base-200 p-6 text-gray-800">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Formula Decay</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">Hidden errors in complex workbooks are silent killers. A single broken cell can erase the margin on a custom build.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card bg-base-200 p-6 text-gray-800">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Market Volatility</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-800">Static data fails when lumber and steel prices fluctuate weekly. Manual updates are too slow for modern bidding.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <figure class="my-12">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1587582423116-ec07293f0395?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&ixid=M3w4NTU2MDF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxyZXNpZGVudGlhbCUyMGNvbnN0cnVjdGlvbnxlbnwwfHx8fDE3NzQ1NDgzNTV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&q=80&w=1080" 
           alt="Professional residential construction site showing framing" 
           class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full">
      <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">
        Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@josholalde?utm_source=leonardo_rails_app&utm_medium=referral">Josh Olalde</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=leonardo_rails_app&utm_medium=referral">Unsplash</a>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl mb-6">The 5-Step Professional Estimating Workflow</h2>
      <p>
        To protect your margins and scale your output, you must standardize your <strong>home construction estimate</strong> process into five distinct, repeatable phases.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 mt-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="badge badge-primary badge-lg">1</span> Standardized Takeoffs
          </h3>
          <p>
            Manual quantity counts are prone to human error and omission. Professional systems utilize digital takeoff tools that integrate directly with the estimate, ensuring that every linear foot of plate and every square foot of drywall is accounted for automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="badge badge-primary badge-lg">2</span> Dynamic Material Pricing
          </h3>
          <p>
            The days of "seasonal pricing" are over. A professional system links your estimate to real-time vendor feeds or a centralized database. When the price of copper spikes, your system should update every active bid instantly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="badge badge-primary badge-lg">3</span> Precision Labor Rates
          </h3>
          <p>
            Estimating labor based on gut feeling or industry averages is a recipe for project delays. Scalable builders use historical productivity data, tracking exactly how many man-hours a specific crew needs for a specific task to build high-confidence bids.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="badge badge-primary badge-lg">4</span> Margin Protection & Contingency
          </h3>
          <p>
            Professional estimates explicitly model overhead recovery and risk. This involves move-beyond-markup strategies, ensuring that indirect costs like project management, insurance, and equipment depreciation are covered in every proposal.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="badge badge-primary badge-lg">5</span> Bid-to-Win Analysis
          </h3>
          <p>
            The process does not end when the bid is submitted. By tracking bid-to-win ratios and variance analysis, where estimated costs are compared to actual costs, builders can identify where they are consistently overpricing or underestimating their work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <figure class="my-12">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1541888946425-d81bb19240f5?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&ixid=M3w4NTU2MDF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjb25zdHJ1Y3Rpb24lMjBzaXRlfGVufDB8fHx8MTc3NDU0ODMzOHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&q=80&w=1080" 
           alt="Construction workers collaborating on site" 
           class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full">
      <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">
        Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@sunburned_surveyor?utm_source=leonardo_rails_app&utm_medium=referral">Scott Blake</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=leonardo_rails_app&utm_medium=referral">Unsplash</a>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl mb-4">Transitioning from Spreadsheet to System</h2>
      <p>
        Moving away from spreadsheets is often more of a cultural challenge than a technical one. It requires the team to trust the data and follow a standardized path. However, the result is a business that is no longer tethered to a single individual's expertise. 
      </p>
      <p>
        By professionalizing your home construction estimate workflow, you create a scalable asset that delivers predictable results, regardless of who is performing the takeoff.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <section class="mt-16 bg-primary text-primary-content p-8 md:p-12 rounded-2xl shadow-xl text-center">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Systematize Your Growth?</h2>
    <p class="text-xl mb-8 opacity-90 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Stop fighting spreadsheets and start building a scalable construction business with precision estimating tools.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
      <%= link_to "Upgrade Your Estimating Workflow", "#", class: "btn btn-secondary btn-lg" %>
      <%= link_to "Book a Strategy Session", "#", class: "btn btn-outline btn-secondary btn-lg bg-white" %>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>